# Kafka Lag Monitor — Slack webhook routing
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# Per-team webhook URLs. If the per-team variable for a team is set,
# alerts for that team are posted there. Otherwise, the system falls
# back to SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL. If neither is set, alerts only appear in
# the in-app feed (still fully demoable).
#
# Create your free workspace (e.g. "lag-monitor-demo") with these
# channels: #pno-team, #catalog-team, #shipping-team. Then add an
# Incoming Webhook integration to each channel and paste the URL here.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------

# Default fallback (used for any team without a specific webhook):
SLACK_WEBHOOK_URL=

# Per-team webhooks (preferred — these are what production routing looks like):
SLACK_WEBHOOK_PNO_TEAM=
SLACK_WEBHOOK_CATALOG_TEAM=
SLACK_WEBHOOK_SHIPPING_TEAM=

# ------------------------------------------------------------------
# On-call mention tags — prepended to the Slack message so the right
# people get pinged. Use Slack's mention syntax:
#   user-group:    <!subteam^S0123ABCD|@pno-oncall>
#   channel-wide:  <!channel>     (default if unset)
#   active-only:   <!here>
# Look up your team's user-group ID in Slack: People & user groups -> select
# the group -> the URL contains the S... ID.
# ------------------------------------------------------------------
SLACK_ONCALL_PNO=
SLACK_ONCALL_CATALOG=
SLACK_ONCALL_SHIPPING=

# Optional server config:
# HOST=0.0.0.0
# PORT=8000
# LAG_MONITOR_DB=lag_monitor.db
